properties.label: Surface
properties.tooltip: The surface to sample with points. Points will be generated in the two dimensional footprint of the combined bounds of the Surface and the Bounding Shape (if any) and then projected onto this surface. If this input is omitted then the network of shapes connected to the Bounding Shape pin will be inspected for a surface shape to use to project the points onto.

properties.label: Bounding Shape
properties.tooltip: All sampled points must be contained within this shape. If this input is omitted then bounds will be taken from the actor so that points are contained within actor bounds. The Unbounded property disables this and instead generates over the entire bounds of Surface.

properties.label: Execution Dependency
properties.tooltip: Data passed to this pin will be used to order execution but will otherwise not contribute to the results of this node.

properties.label: Overrides
properties.tooltip: Atribute Set containing multiple parameters to override. Names must match perfectly.

properties.label: PointsPerSquaredMeter
properties.tooltip:
Controls the grid cell size, down to a minimum size defined by the Point Extents.
Attribute type is "float" and its exact name is "PointsPerSquaredMeter"

properties.label: PointExtents
properties.tooltip:
Extents of the points to create (e.g. half their total size)
Attribute type is "FVector" and its exact name is "PointExtents"

properties.label: Looseness
properties.tooltip:
Controls how points are placed in their cell with 0 being in the center and 1 being anywhere inside the full cell size.
Attribute type is "float" and its exact name is "Looseness"

properties.label: bUnbounded
properties.tooltip:
If no Bounding Shape input is provided, the actor bounds are used to limit the sample generation domain.
This option allows ignoring the actor bounds and generating over the entire surface. Use with caution as this
may generate a lot of points.
Attribute type is "bool" and its exact name is "bUnbounded"

properties.label: bApplyDensityToPoints
properties.tooltip: Attribute type is "bool" and its exact name is "bApplyDensityToPoints"

properties.label: PointSteepness
properties.tooltip:
Each PCG point represents a discretized, volumetric region of world space. The points' Steepness value [0.0 to
1.0] establishes how "hard" or "soft" that volume will be represented. From 0, it will ramp up linearly
increasing its influence over the density from the point's center to up to two times the bounds. At 1, it will
represent a binary box function with the size of the point's bounds.
Attribute type is "float" and its exact name is "PointSteepness"

properties.label: bSampleVirtualTextureNormals

Controls whether the landscape will try to sample normals from a normals virtual texture (if it exists), otherwise computes normals from multiple height samples. Only relevant to GPU sampling.
